                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> <lb n="1"/>e<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan> Aur<supplied reason="lost">elius</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="3"/>nobiliss<supplied reason="lost">imu</supplied>s <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Caes</abbr><ex>ar</ex></expan>? <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied> <lb n="4"/>a <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>oetovione</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>ilia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>assuum</ex></expan> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Erwähnt ist vermutlich Severus Alexander (&amp;apos;M(arcus) Aur(elius) [Severus Alexander] / nobiliss[imu]s [Caes(ar) ---]&amp;apos;). Denkbar wären auch Numerianus und Carinus, für Geta scheint zuwenig Platz in der vorhergehenden Zeile zu sein. Mögliche Ergänzung auch &amp;apos;M(arcus) Aur(elius) [Carinus]&amp;apos;. Z. 5: AP-Ligatur.</p>
            </div>
